USING CELLS AS MICROSCOPES TO DIAGNOSE & CURE DISEASES: A MAJOR GOAL OF THE CHAN ZUCKERBERG INITIATIVE (CZI)‚Ä¢
-
On the episode of the Huberman Lab podcast out today I interview @zuck & @priscillachan - Co-Founders of the @chanzuckerberginitiative - a philanthropic organization whose goal is to help scientists cure all human disease by the end of this century. 
-
Here we are discussing one of their major projects underway: to develop technologies that allow individual cells of the body to act as microscopes- traveling to and analyzing exactly what needs to be repaired within diseased organs, and then directing those repairs. We also discuss the recent expansion of the Chan Zuckerberg Initiative to include new Biohubs in Chicago and New York.
-
Later, Mark and I talk more about the tools and resources @meta has developed to help people control and understand their online experiences. We also discuss their latest progress with mixed reality and what‚Äôs possible with the Quest 3 and Ray Ban Meta Smart Glasses. 
-
You can find the episode in all formats by going to hubermanlab.com
-
Please put any questions you might have in the comments section below this post and as always, thank you for your interest in science! 
-
#meta #chanzuckerberginitiative #biology #medicine

Priscilla and I just shared that CZI is launching our third Biohub in New York with the goal to engineer immune cells to detect and treat diseases earlier. Researchers will study how to program immune cells to identify early signs of disease that are currently missed by our immune system and make targeted repairs to stop those diseases before they progress. They'll also look at applying this technology to diseases that are hard to detect early like pancreatic and ovarian cancers, Alzheimer's and Parkinson's. We're really excited to see progress on this new work.
